{"title": "Permissive context mode for resources", "summary": "  Creating world-readable and -writeable files poses a serious security risk. It is for this reason that the `Context.MODE_WORLD_READABLE` and `Context.MODE_WORLD_WRITEABLE` constants were deprecated and later removed. ", "description": "\n\nCreating world-readable and -writeable files poses a serious security risk.\nIt is for this reason that the `Context.MODE_WORLD_READABLE` and `Context.MODE_WORLD_WRITEABLE` constants were deprecated and later removed.\n", "recommendations": "\n\n\u2705 Use Context.MODE_PRIVATE wherever possible\n\n\u2705 Use a `ContentProvider` when sharing content with other applications\n\n\u274c (For legacy applications) Do not use the deprecated `MODE_WORLD_READABLE` or `MODE_WORLD_WRITEABLE` constants\n", "taxonomy": ["CWE-276"], "references": ["https://docs.bearer.com/reference/rules/java_android_world_readable_writable_mode"], "details": "{% include '../generic_bandit_issue/details' %}"}